g.text: File Cabinet: There it still is -- inviting you to...
File Cabinet: The file cabinet stands steady as ever and the unlocked drawer slides out to greet you.
Logic: The *special* borscht seems a bit odd in the list.
Volition: You're trying hard, but the data here is *unbelievably* dry. Something about containers...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Is that what you're doing with those folders over there?"
You: Could I actually focus through *not* focusing?
Esprit de Corps: ...let's see what's inside, he thinks.
File Cabinet: Hundreds of documents containing logistical data. Two kinds of transactions stand out: materials coming into Revachol from the outside world -- from Mundi, Graad, and even Iilmaraa...

Volition: Whatever's hidden here is hidden well. Concentration isn't enough, only a trained accountant, with a background in logistics, would be able to *really* make sense of it. However there *is* a little hand-written note, stuck on the side of the drawer.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Good." He turns away from the file cabinet. "This is probably not relevant to our case anyway. After all, we are not investigating an accounting mystery."
Kim Kitsuragi: "It's *unfortunate* for the Union to just leave their paperwork lying around like this..."
File Cabinet: It's hard to make sense of this thicket of company names, dates, quantities, and percentages. You try to focus, but the lines are getting blurry...
You: "If I let my eyes go completely out of focus, all shapes start melting into each other."
You: Leave the folders alone for now.
File Cabinet: It appears to be a to-do list written in large, uneven capital letters:
File Cabinet: You already went through all of these.
You: Force yourself to go through the folders.
File Cabinet: The file cabinet stands steady as ever. Sliding out a drawer presents you the folders you already went through. On top of them is the handwritten note.
Take another look at the note.
You: (Turn to the lieutenant.) "Look, Kim, a to-do note with a list of errands for *Evrart*."
File Cabinet: ...and the same materials being handed over to companies inside Revachol. Couron, Coal City, La Delta, and Jamrock are listed among the many districts where the imports are being sold.
Electrochemistry: What is so special about this *borscht*? Code for drugs? Booze? Blood?
File Cabinet: On second glance, someone has forgotten to properly close one of the drawers.
File Cabinet: The drawer opens smoothly. Inside is a well-organized selection of brown folders.
Kim Kitsuragi: "The leader of the Débardeurs' Union, Evrart Claire, has someone running errands for him." He points to the list. "Nothing incriminating here, though."
"Evrart has someone running errands for him." He points to the list. "Nothing incriminating here, though."
"The Débardeurs' Union leader, Evrart Claire, has Leo running errands for him." He points to the list. "Nothing incriminating here, though."
"Evrart has Leo running errands for him." He points to the list. "Nothing incriminating here, though."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Right." The lieutenant's expression stiffens. "This is probably not relevant to our case. After all, we are not investigating an accounting mystery."
File Cabinet: The drawer slides shut smoothly.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Evrart Claire, probably -- the head of the Débardeurs' Union." He inspects the note. "One of his aides must have left it. Nothing incriminating here."
He inspects the note. "One of his aides must have left it. Nothing incriminating here."
"Evrart Claire, probably -- the head of the Débardeurs' Union." He inspects the note. "Leo must have left it. Nothing incriminating here."
He inspects the note. "Leo must have left it. Nothing incriminating here."
Volition: You are a police officer, not a spiritual healer. You can focus the normal way by turning your attention to something and not letting go.
You: "Never mind the note." (Close the drawer.)
Volition: Look how blurry all the lines on these papers are -- how unwieldy your own willpower is to yourself. You're like an absurdist Samaran monk -- focusing through not focusing.
File Cabinet: All items on the list have been crossed out and the note itself is crumpled.
File Cabinet: All items on the list have been crossed out and the note itself is crumpled.
Inland Empire: Doesn't look too incriminating -- but still feels like a *find*.
Conceptualization: Hermeneutics was almost within your grasp, but now only vague letters float before your eyes. Less meaningful, but aesthetically more pleasing.
File Cabinet: The drawer slides shut smoothly.
You: "Let's just get back to work, lieutenant."
Kim Kitsuragi: "My thought exactly, officer." He turns away from the file cabinet. "Shall we?"
